# Kelimelik AI Project Rules

You are working on Kelimelik AI, an Expo React Native + TypeScript + Supabase vocabulary learning app.

Core stack:
- Expo React Native
- TypeScript
- Expo Router
- Supabase Auth, DB, RLS, Edge Functions
- OpenAI must only be used through Supabase Edge Functions
- Never put OpenAI API keys in frontend code

Important product rules:
- Word adding must stay fast and low-friction.
- Do not add confirmation steps for every word.
- Only show correction/confirmation when the typed word is suspicious or AI suggests a meaningfully different word.
- “Yazdığım gibi ekle” means: add exactly what the user typed, do not generate AI content, and do not show cached AI content for that user word.
- Practice info must not be shown in Word Detail.
- Fill-in-the-blank belongs only in practice screens.
- Do not add fake Google login, fake language selector, or fake forgot-password flows unless real backend support exists.

Design rules:
- Warm cream / terracotta / orange visual language.
- Avoid generic blue SaaS UI.
- Use rounded premium mobile cards.
- Keep the app feeling simple, friendly, and focused.

Development rules:
- Inspect files before patching.
- Prefer small patches.
- After every patch, run:
  npx tsc --noEmit
- Check git status before and after changes.
- Do not touch Supabase migrations or Edge Functions without explaining why.
- Do not change database shape casually.
- Do not remove existing AI/Supabase infrastructure unless explicitly asked.